The K2-133 Exoplanetary System


Overview

K2-133 is a star with 0.46 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.46 times its radius. It is located 245.27 light years away from the solar system.

K2-133 is known to have 4 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the K2-133 system


K2-133 e

K2-133 e was discovered by the K2 observatory using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.13 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The radius of K2-133 e is 1.73 that of Earth.
